==Translingual==

===Etymology===
The character [[弗]] ([[Pinyin]]: fú) originally depicted a misshaped arrow on a bow that needed to be straightened.  Later, it took on the meaning of "to straighten" or "to correct."  Since its sound also matches the sound for "no," this character was also used to represent the concept of "no."  However, in modern Chinese, the characters [[不]] ([[Pinyin]]: bù) and [[否]] ([[Pinyin]]: fǒu) are far more common.

